<indexterm><primary>xdg-user-dir</primary></indexterm><indexterm><primary>Get the path used for desktop user directory location.</primary></indexterm>
<refnamediv id="xdg-user-dir-1-name"><refname>xdg-user-dir</refname><refpurpose>Get the path used for desktop user directory location.</refpurpose></refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv id="xdg-user-dir-1-synp"><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>&cmd;</command>
<arg choice="plain"><replaceable>DIR</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1 id="xdg-user-dir-1-desc"><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para><command>&cmd;</command> is a utility that extracts the location of the specified desktop user directory from the file :
</para>
<para>
    <literal>${HOME}/.config/user-dirs.dirs</literal>
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="xdg-user-dir-1-oper"><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<para>Valid desktop directories (<replaceable>DIR</replaceable>) are:

        DESKTOP
        DOWNLOAD
        TEMPLATES
        PUBLICSHARE
        DOCUMENTS
        MUSIC
        PICTURES
        VIDEOS

If an invalid directory is requested ${HOME} is returned.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="xdg-user-dir-1-envr"><title>&envr-tt;</title>
<para>See <citerefentry><refentrytitle>environ</refentrytitle><manvolnum>
5</manvolnum></citerefentry> for descriptions of the following environment
variables: 
</para>
<para>
    HOME.
</para>

<para>
Other environment variable that are used are:
</para>
<variablelist termlength="short">
<varlistentry>
<term>XDG_CONFIG_HOME</term>
<listitem><para>Base directory for storge of XDG configuration files. Defaults to <filename>${HOME}/.config</filename></para></listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="xdg-user-dir-1-file"><title>&file-tt;</title>
<para>The following files are used by this application:</para>
<variablelist termlength="short">

<varlistentry>
<term><filename>/usr/bin/&cmd;</filename></term>
<listitem><para>XDG Directory expansion utility.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry>
<term><filename>${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/user-dirs.dirs</filename></term>
<listitem><para>Location of the user-specific configuration including the current
list of directories and what they map to.</para></listitem>
</varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</refsect1>

<refsect1 id="xdg-user-dir-1-exam"><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example role="example">
<title>Location of user's documents directory</title>
<para>
<userinput>% &cmd; DOCUMENTS</userinput>
<screen>/home/user/Documents</screen>
</para>
</example>

</refsect1>


